text: Treis-Sants-en-Ouche is a commune in the Eure department in Normandy in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint-Aubin-le-Vertueux (the seat), Saint-Clair-d'Arcey and Saint- Quentin-des-Isles.Arrêté préfectoral 25 September 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Eure department ==References== Category:Communes of Eure
title: Treis-Sants-en-Ouche
